5831, "(fr)Report, Ensign! What happened?"

5832, "(fr)Sir...Aria was hit, sir. Just as we exited hyperspace. Heavy damage to all systems."

5833, "(fr)Attempting to restore bridge control systems...stand by."

5834, "(fr)Lieutenant Ryan, check the bridge for injuries. Ensign Holmes, I want a status report!"

5835, "(fr)Helm controls are offline. Weapons and sensors offline. Communications offline. Astrogation offline. Life support running on emergency power."

5836, "(fr)How is Commander Cameron?"

5837, "(fr)The commander's unconscious. Her injuries need stabilising. I'll do what I can but we need to get her to the medbay."

5838, "(fr)And LC Ellis? "

5839, "(fr)Dead, sir."

5840, "(fr)Sir, I've managed to get internal ship communications working. Engineering is on the line."

5841, "(fr)Then...who's left? Chief Engineer Hughes? ...he won't leave Engineering, not like this. Lieutenant Kelly? Lieutenant Ryan?"

5842, "(fr)It's me, isn't it?"

5843, "(fr)Yes sir. You're the next senior officer. "

5844, "(fr)Right...ok. Lieutenant Ryan, once you've stabilised Commander Cameron, take your position on the helm. Lieutenant Kelly, see if you can raise the rest of the ship."

5845, "(fr)Engineering to bridge. Anyone alive up there? It's a bloody mess down here but we've just managed to restore main power."

5846, "(fr)Hughes, this is Ross. Be advised the commander's unconscious and the XO is dead. I'm taking command of the bridge."

5847, "(fr)Copy Lieutenant Commander. Could be worse I suppose. In a few seconds we'll reroute power to the fusion engines. You'll know if it works. Engineering out."

5848, "(fr)Sir! I've got green lights on helm control."

5849, "(fr)RCS seems to be working. I should be able to input course changes now."

5850, "(fr)Face a direction, and press $Spacebar$ (Secondary Fire) to change course in that direction."

5851, "(fr)Aye sir, changing course."

5852, "(fr)Course change order received."

5853, "(fr)Aye sir, inputting new coordinates."

5854, "(fr)Copy helm order."

5855, "(fr)Switching course."

5856, "(fr)Power has been restored to ship systems. Access lifts and transporters now online."

5857, "(fr)Thank you Ensign. Get a team to transport Commander Cameron to the medbay as a first priority."

5858, "(fr)Repair teams are now moving through the ship doing what they can to fix the damage. We should see more systems coming online soon."

5859, "(fr)Sensors are now online."

5860, "(fr)Start sensor sweeps. We don't know if whoever attacked us is still out there. Where are we?"

5861, "(fr)We're in proximity to the Andaman nav transponder. No other ships in the immediate area."

5862, "(fr)Sir, comms traffic is quiet. Trying to contact Katherine Lau but the dust clouds are making it difficult."

5863, "(fr)What are your orders, sir?"

5864, "(fr)Orders? I don't know. I...wouldn't even know where to start. This is different to being in a cockpit."

5865, "(fr)I wouldn't even know the first thing about running a ship."

5866, "(fr)Sir, we don't expect you to run the ship."

5867, "(fr)Aria has a fine crew who know what they need to do. We'll do the job. We just need you to give us a direction."

5868, "(fr)No one knows everything, sir. That's what we're here for. Our job is to give you the information to make the right decision."

5869, "(fr)Well, ok. Let's get to it then. To your stations. See what our options are."

5870, "(fr)Downloading transponder data. We've got a map of the surrounding area. Andaman Anchorage is nearby with field repair facilities. It's unmanned."

5871, "(fr)Andaman Station is fourteen klicks from the anchorage. There's been heavy Combine-flagged traffic in the area over the past twenty four hours."

5872, "(fr)Sir, the anchorage is unmanned but automated systems are active. Aria can undergo more comprehensive field repairs."

5873, "(fr)Press $2$ to call for repair drones."

