5881, "(fr)Weapons control is now online. Hull integrity stabilised. Aria is combat ready, sir."

5882, "(fr)What's the status of Commander Cameron?"

5883, "(fr)One moment. Patching you through to medbay."

5884, "(fr)Ross, this is Dr McGill. The commander is in a coma and we're still stabilising her. If you've got something important to say tell me now, otherwise let my staff do their work."

5885, "(fr)Well...that's it then. I guess it's all on me. No one else to help."

5886, "(fr)Sir, our orders were to bring back Lau and Erikson. Do we continue the mission or return home?"

5887, "(fr)Sir, there's an ASM platform near our hyperspace exit point. It's inactive. Ship logs show that it was the one that attacked Aria."

5888, "(fr)The area is clear of shipping for now. I think it's a good target if you wanted to test out weapons functionality."

5889, "(fr)Remote turrets fully functional, sir. Weapons control at one hundred percent effectiveness."

5890, "(fr)Ok. We're limping, with casualties and in a hostile environment. But we're still going. Our mission still stands. "

5891, "(fr)We're King's Officers, sir. There is no duty that we do not honour, no mission that we abandon. The crew of HMS Aria will follow you."

5892, "(fr)We'll find those bastards who hit us, and give them a right hiding! Sir."

5893, "(fr)We need to find our people and bring them back. But the ones who tried to kill us are still out there. They'll likely give us another go."

5894, "(fr)Give the order, and we'll make Aria battle-ready."

5895, "(fr)All right. Lieutenant Kelly, set battle stations! We're going in!"

5896, "(fr)Main plasma turrets have a range of 3000m"

