5906, "(fr)What's going on? A lockdown? Is the Combine responsible?"

5907, "(fr)Get Andaman Control. Ask them what's going on."

5908, "(fr)Andaman Station, this is HMS Aria of the Crown Navy. Please advise your situation. What is the reason for the lockdown? "

5909, "(fr)Crown Navy warship Aria. The station has been locked down under orders from the Sinarus Combine Navy."

5910, "(fr)The Combine fleet are enforcing the lockdown with armed troops. They say they are hunting fugitives, and that no one is to leave the station while they conduct the search."

5911, "(fr)Fugitives? Did they give the names of who they're looking for, Andaman?"

5912, "(fr)No names. Master Batra offered the help of station security services, but the Combine refused to give any details of the individuals in question. The lack of information in addition to the lockdown has become a cause for agitation."

5913, "(fr)Not being transparent? Does that sound like something the Combine would do? Let me talk to them."

5914, "(fr)Andaman Station, this is Stuart Ross, CO of Aria. We are here to provide asylum for two individuals who may be on board. They may be the ones the Combine are looking for."

5915, "(fr)If you help us find and evacuate them, it may bring about the end of the lockdown."

5916, "(fr)Sinarussian troops are all over the station and their warships will likely come back soon. We don't want to be the target of Combine retributions if we help you."

5917, "(fr)Leave the Combine to us, Andaman. Ross out."

5918, "(fr)Sir. I'm not discounting Aria's combat ability but if there's a significant Combine asset out here, we may not be able to resolve an engagement."

5919, "(fr)Yes Ensign. I know. But if we manage to get our people quickly, we'll be out of here before any such engagement takes place."

5920, "(fr)Two Combine Light Attack Craft are on an intercept! Recommend evasive manoeuvring to avoid their heavy cannons!"

5921, "(fr)Combine LACs destroyed!"

5922, "(fr)We can assist, but finding details of their arrival will be difficult. The Combine have commandeered our computer systems and locked us out of our own records."

5923, "(fr)Well, we better make it quick. The Combine marines will have definitely noticed our arrival. Wouldn't surprise me if they're already on comms to their friends."

5924, "(fr)Alert! Khopesh-class frigate on sensors, she's moving to engage us!"

5925, "(fr)Solomnent frigate is spooling her impeller. Looks like we mauled her badly."

5926, "(fr)Combine frigate destroyed, sir. Catastrophic detonation."

5927, "(fr)Sir, I may be able to access the Andaman records remotely. Aria has powerful comms technology, it's how we managed to defuse the nuclear device at Covenant."

5928, "(fr)If we get close enough to the docking berths for a remote scan, I may be able to find an access point to their systems."

5929, "(fr)I've got them! Section 35-C, room 281. Rental accommodation under the pseudonym Noemi Pasquale, biometric record matches Lau. Confined to their room until the lockdown ends."

5930, "(fr)Can you get in contact with them?"

5931, "(fr)Aye sir. A simple case of an external comms directly to their room's terminal. One second."

5932, "(fr)HMS Aria, is that you?"

5933, "(fr)Lau? This is Stuart Ross. Are you and Erikson okay? And...Pasquale?"

5934, "(fr)Stuart? It's good to see you again. The name was Erikson's idea, in case we got tracked. I guess it turned out to be useful. Where is Anil Cameron?"

5935, "(fr)We were attacked on arrival to Andaman and suffered casualties. Cameron is incapacitated. I'm acting CO."

5936, "(fr)Wow Ross, your first command. You know, being captain of a ship kinda suits you. I'm glad you're ok."

5937, "(fr)Right. We need to get you and Erikson out of Andaman and onto Aria. Can both of you make it to a docking ring?"

5938, "(fr)Security's locked down the entire station, and Combine troops are crawling all over. Not without overriding the security lock or getting the lockdown lifted."

5939, "(fr)Stand by Lau. I'll get back to you when we've got a plan."

