5983, "(fr)Well everyone, I'm willing to take suggestions."

5984, "(fr)Those Combine guns are powerful, but slow. If Lieutenant Ryan can keep us evasive and unpredictable, we can minimise incoming damage."

5985, "(fr)I suggest we carve up the Combine formation piecemeal, instead of engaging them all at once. Strikers and LACs first, to give us time to plan our engagement with the destroyers."

5986, "(fr)Sir, our plasma cannons don't do much against warship hulls but they burn through subsystem and turret armour like no one's business."

5987, "(fr)Might I suggest keeping distance until they send their strike wings at us. Once we've dealt with them, we make best speed to the destroyers and take out their fire control."

5988, "(fr)Lau...what's the deal with Erikson? Why are the Combine hunting her too?"

5989, "(fr)It's ok Lau. It's time Ross knew the truth. There's no need to hide anymore."

5990, "(fr)Ross, I was a senior developer in one of the Sinarus advanced weapons research departments. My team helped develop the burst anti-ship missile for the arsenal ships."

5991, "(fr)I heard rumours of a terrible weapon called 'Black Sun' but it wasn't until Morik that the full horror was revealed. I had to leave. I left the Combine under an alias."

5992, "(fr)I knew Black Sun originated in the Veil, so I came to Sulsia to try to stop it, somehow. I joined up with Lau on the Hoshikuzu. And the rest you now know."

5993, "(fr)Of course. That's why the admiral needs Erikson. She's the key to Kakotchka's arsenal ships."

5994, "(fr)I'm sorry I couldn't tell you earlier Stuart. Erikson told me after we left Sulsia, and asked me to keep it private."

5995, "(fr)Corvette Aria, there are Combine warships near our station and we have no weapons to defend ourselves. We need you to drive them off."

5996, "(fr)Thank you for protecting my station, Alban. Whatever happens next, you can always count on Andaman's friendship."

